Begin RFC:
RFC: 0.0.0
Title: Contribution Guidelines
Author: Richeve Bebedor <richeve.bebedor+vs-scripts@gmail.com>
Status: Draft
Created: 2025-12-20

1. Introduction:

   We welcome contributions to the install-node-version script! This document
   outlines the standards and processes for contributing to the project.

2. Workflow:

   2.1. Fork the repository.
   2.2. Create a new branch for your feature or bug fix.
   2.3. Ensure your code follows the 83-character column limit specified in
        .editorconfig.
   2.4. Add detailed PowerShell Comment-Based Help to any new functions.
   2.5. Update the CHANGELOG as needed.
   2.6. Submit a Pull Request.

3. Standards:

   Please refer to the README for technical specifications and design goals.
   Maintaining the RFC-style documentation and modular function design is
   mandatory for all contributions.
End RFC:
